      "content": "Eugenicists in the early 20th century used a variety of pseudoscientific metrics and theories to support their claims. They often relied on flawed intelligence testing, which was biased towards Western, educated, industrialized, rich, and democratic (WEIRD) populations, and thus did not accurately reflect the intelligence of other racial groups. They also used craniometry, the measurement of skull size and shape, to claim that certain races had larger, supposedly more \"advanced\" brains. Additionally, they cited eugenicist theories that linked moral and behavioral traits, such as criminality or laziness, to racial characteristics. These theories were used to argue for policies like forced sterilizations and immigration restrictions, under the guise of improving the human race. It is important to note that these ideas were based on deeply flawed and biased science, and have been thoroughly discredited.",
